      "question": "Prove that the lengths of tangents drawn from an external point to a circle are equal.",
      "answer": "The lengths of tangents $PA$ and $PB$ are equal as $\\triangle OAP \\cong \\triangle OBP$ by RHS congruence.",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Draw a circle with center $O$ and an external point $P$.",
          "Let $PA$ and $PB$ be two tangents from $P$ touching the circle at $A$ and $B$ respectively.",
          "Join $OA$, $OB$, and $OP$.",
          "In $\\triangle OAP$ and $\\triangle OBP$, observe that $OA = OB$ (radii of the same circle).",
          "$OP = OP$ (common side).",
          "$\\angle OAP = \\angle OBP = 90^\\circ$ (radius is perpendicular to tangent at point of contact).",
          "By RHS congruence criterion, $\\triangle OAP \\cong \\triangle OBP$.",
          "Hence, $PA = PB$ by CPCT."
        ],
        "derivation": "$In \\ \\triangle OAP \\ and \\ \\triangle OBP, \\\\ OA = OB \\ (radii), \\\\ OP = OP \\ (common), \\\\ \\angle OAP = \\angle OBP = 90^\\circ \\ (tangent \\perp radius), \\\\ \\triangle OAP \\cong \\triangle OBP \\ (RHS), \\\\ \\therefore PA = PB \\ (CPCT)$"
      },
